^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|OK, let us go over double and correct. The problem that needs to be solved is how you show a real strong hand after an opponent opens. It is rare that you have that strong a hand after someone else opens, but it does happen on occasion. The solution to that problem is "double and correct."  A simple overcall limits your hand to 15 or so. But, if you make a takeout double, and then "correct" partner's suit to a suit of your own, that shows a strong hand. Typically, that would show around 16-19 points and a 5 card suit.|
