nt||HT|d|at|{|ia|,1dxp1sp2c|at|}|HT|A|cp|8|AT|^L@2^Z@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|So if the auction went as on the left, liza would be showing 16-19 points with very good clubs and that is a typical double and correct auction. It is not forcing, but responder with as little as 4 or 5 points, especially with a fit, should keep bidding. After the 1@S bid liza had an even better hand so she bid 3@C, which shows at least 20 or so. It rarely happens that you have 20 after an opener. If you think about it, that leaves very little for partner. |
