nt||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|As to what liza should do over 3@S, there is no clear cut answer. However, assuming the clubs are divided evenly among the other 3 hands, an 8 card club fit is quite possible and even if lisa has only 1 club, they might split 3-3. And lisa might also have a diamond card on a good day, so they might have 2 diamond stoppers. All in all, liza can be a bit optimistic and see that 9 tricks are  very possible, so 3N is a good gamble.|
PG| ***** 158 ***** |


nt||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|In general, as I said before, you should tend to favor the 3N game over 5 of a minor. There are occasionally hands where you lack stoppers, and 5 of a minor makes and 3N does not. But for the most part, if you can make 5 of a minor, you can often make 3N. so avoid bidding 5 of a minor unless you are pretty sure you lack a stopper in a suit.|
